---
/**
 * storage-engines · storage-engines-fundamentals · Figure 4 — Level 3, an
 * absent-key LSM read using Bloom filters to skip SSTables.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source page (figure + svg + figcaption). References
 * marker-end="url(#arw)", so the grey #arw marker is inlined here in a local
 * <defs> (verbatim from the source defs block) so it resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A read for an absent key uses a Bloom filter to skip SSTables that definitely lack it"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="10" y="50" width="96" height="44" rx="9" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text x="58" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >read user:9</text
            >
            <text x="58" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">absent key</text>
            <line x1="106" y1="72" x2="146" y2="72" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <!-- bloom gates -->
            <g font-size="9.5">
                <rect x="150" y="20" width="120" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text x="210" y="39" text-anchor="middle" fill="#244a2e"
                    >SST-3 · "absent" → skip</text
                >
                <rect x="150" y="58" width="120" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect><text x="210" y="77" text-anchor="middle" fill="#244a2e"
                    >SST-2 · "absent" → skip</text
                >
                <rect x="150" y="96" width="120" height="30" rx="6" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect><text x="210" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7a2218"
                    >SST-1 · "probably" → open</text
                >
            </g>
            <text x="210" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Bloom filter: one-sided error</text
            >
            <line x1="272" y1="111" x2="340" y2="111" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <rect x="344" y="96" width="96" height="30" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect><text x="392" y="115" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5">1 disk read</text>
            <text x="470" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >"definitely absent"</text
            >
            <text x="470" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >is never wrong →</text
            >
            <text x="470" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >skipping is safe</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Without filters an absent-key read touches every SSTable. A ~1%-FPR filter costs ~10
        bits/key and turns that into one rare false-positive open.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
